The paper discusses a new method for parallelizing the training of convolutional neural networks, which is a common topic in machine learning and computer vision research. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). Additionally, the paper mentions that their method improves the scaling of convolutional neural networks, which suggests that it may also be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
